<p>

<b>Chez Bruce</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../437/26437.xml">
restaurant</link> located at 2 Bellevue Road in <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../365/94365.xml">
Wandsworth</link></site>
, <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../867/17867.xml">
London</link></village>
, <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../316/9316.xml">
England</link></country>
.  The restaurant was opened in February, 1995 by Bruce Poole and his business partner Nigel Platts-Martin.</p>
<p>

Platts-Martin is proprietor of several other London restaurants including: La Trompette in <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../931/93931.xml">
Chiswick</link></site>
, The Glasshouse in <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../142/94142.xml">
Kew</link></site>
, The Ledbury in <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../200/94200.xml">
Notting Hill</link></site>
 and The Square in <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../167/94167.xml">
Mayfair</link></site>
.</p>
<p>

